genresAdvancedInfo.name: marimba
genresAdvancedInfo.description: The marimba is a percussion instrument that originated in Africa and is now commonly used in Latin American music. It consists of a set of wooden bars that are struck with mallets to produce different tones. Marimba music is known for its lively rhythms and intricate melodies, and is often used in traditional folk music and dances. The marimba has also been incorporated into other genres such as jazz and classical music.
